message.content:
He was better, he had made a
miraculous recovery and Sandra would
soon be his wife. The Devil, he thought,
certainly looked after his own.
Something in Sandra's attitude struck
him suddenly, making him say:
"You can't forgive him for this -
can you?" "forgive is an unchaste,
patronizing word,' she replied. 'I despise
the deceit. The lie.'
